content: Open Source iALL Earthship designs.    The most brilliant, creative and forward thinkers of the 21st century are encouraging open source; not just for software, but for everything.  The Internet Age has shown everyone that the traditional patent system slows, limits and even halts development.  More and more brilliant people (like Linux, Elon Musk, Mark Zuckerberg) are "Copy-Lefting" their ideas.  It is doubtful patents will become obsolete, but patented technologies will certainly fall far behind their open source counter-parts and it will be difficult for them to compete.  Tesla Motors - Our Patents Belong to you. "Technology leadership is not defined by patents, which history has repeatedly shown to be small protection indeed against a determined competitor, but rather by the ability of a company to attract and motivate the worldâ€™s most talented engineers. We believe in applying the open source philosophy."  How Will Zuckerberg Rule the World? By Giving Tech Away "The real goal is to build the community. A lot of times, the best way to advance the technology is to work on it asa community."

content: Great app in my opinion, you can never have too much information of course but this is a great start and well worth the $9.99. I have just become interested in the earthship concept and was initially bummed when I saw that the plans cost so much...then I realized this app had been released. The idea of the app and making the info more open source is awesome guys. I'm sure you will ultimately reach more people this way and raise more funds just due to the sheer number who will be helped tremendously by this app. Please keep adding more information and perhaps other designs and sustainable concepts. Cheers from Australia :)

I'm rooting for the Earthship Academy, now in its 5th full year.  The disaster relief models that the  team and students have built around the world are homes that will withstand emergencies and provide comfort year round.  If you want to free yourself from utilities, insure yourself against a changing climate, and contribute to the very deserving efforts of the people who've put this earthship app and the whole idea together, i think $10 is a deal. Photo resolution is perfect if you follow instructions.
